<br>
Rather than allowing players to loot pets, which was suggested in other posts and could conceivably be used to exploit NO DROP code, why not allow the pet masters to inspect their pets?<br>
<br>
This way the pet masters could see what items the pets will/wont equip, and in which slots?  Would allow Necros/Mages to really begin to understand what they should equip their pets with, and clear up so many conflicting urban myths.<br>
<br>
There are two ways I could see this being implimented:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  Using the same inspect code that is already used against players would allow you to see exactly what slots items are in.<br>
<br>
This would be my preferred method, as it would allow you to inspect items and see statistics.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.  /pet inventory , a new command that would show inventory like this:<br>
<br>
I am wearing these items master:<br>
Chest: Phantom Plate Breastplate<br>
LWrist: Phantom Plate Bracer<br>
RWrist: Phantom Plate Bracer<br>
Legs: Phantom Plate Legs<br>
Primary: Sword of Runes<br>
Secondary: Sword of Runes<br>
Range: Shard of the Core<br>
<br>
Downside of this second method is that you wouldn't be able to inspect the items, and compare stats, and as the epic (and possibly other pets?) come pre-equipped with armor, you would have no way of knowing the quality of these items.<br>
<br>
Comments? <p><FONT SIZE="3" COLOR=#FFFFFF FACE="Comic Sans MS, Sans-Serif, Courier New, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">
