<br>
The items information has been leeked/tested/viewed on a pets corpse before.  It won't make too much difference to high level players, but all those beginning EverQuest and starting a pet class (Magician, Necro &amp; Beast primarily) or rerolling their other characters to start a pet class would be able to observe these details for themselves with relative ease, as opposed to having to resort to external sites for the same sort of information.<br>
<br>
I don't see anything wrong with making the basics like &quot;When can my pet duel weild?&quot; and &quot;Will my pet wear his haste mask?&quot; visible to the player within the game world.  And if it was only visible to the player themselves, I don't see it putting a whole lot of extra load on the servers (ie: a whole raid won't be constantly inspecting your pet, they'd just end up /consider'ing it instead). <p><FONT SIZE="3" COLOR=#FFFFFF FACE="Comic Sans MS, Sans-Serif, Courier New, Verdana, Arial, Helvetica">
